additional_information: Inhalation of dust generated during grinding, sanding, or machining may cause irritation of the respiratory system, with symptoms including cough, sneezing, nasal discharge, headache, hoarseness, and nose or throat pain.
Mechanical skin irritation may occur, with symptoms including abrasion, redness, pain, and itching.
Allergic skin reactions in sensitive individuals may include redness, swelling, blistering, and itching.
Mechanical eye irritation may occur, with symptoms including pain, redness, tearing, and corneal abrasion.
Ingestion may cause physical blockage with symptoms including cramping, abdominal pain, and constipation.
